Package: stppSim
Type: Package
Title: Spatiotemporal Point Patterns Simulation
Version: 1.3.2
Author: Monsuru Adepeju [cre, aut]
Maintainer: Monsuru Adepeju <monsuur2010@yahoo.com>
Description: Generates artificial point patterns marked by their
  spatial and temporal signatures. The generated point cloud
  may include inherent interactions between both signatures.
  The simulation process is achieved through the integration of 
  microsimulation (Holm, E., (2017)<doi:10.1002/9781118786352.wbieg0320>) 
  and agent-based models (Bonabeau, E., (2002)<doi:10.1073/pnas.082080899>). 
  The simulation process is initiated by configuring the movement
  characteristics of the specified agents (called 'walkers') and how
  they interact within the simulation environment. 
  These interactions (Quaglietta, L. and Porto, M., 
  (2019)<doi:10.1186/s40462-019-0154-8>) ensures the realisation of 
  and time domains result in specific spatiotemporal point patterns 
  spatiotemporal patterns which can be visualized, analyzed, and/or
  deployed for various analytical purposes. Given the growing scarcity 
  of detailed spatiotemporal data in a wide range of domains, this 
  package offers an alternative data source for use several domains, 
  including social and life sciences.
